         <abstract id="aspace_bd19f42d2836a521995a9c6fbbe09d80">Ella Gertrude Clanton Thomas was the
            wife of Jefferson Thomas, Confederate officer and Georgia planter. This collection
            contains diaries, partially unbound, for the years 1848-1849, 1851-1852, 1855-1859,
            1861-1866, 1868-1871, and 1878-1889, with the first volume in a different hand from the
            rest. Typed copies of the diaries are also included. The entries describe in detail Mrs.
            Thomas' reading; studies at Macon Female College (now called Wesleyan College) in Macon,
            Ga.; conversion to methodism; clothing and dress styles; gossip and social life;
            shopping and prices; church services; courtship by and marriage to Jefferson Thomas; and
            plantation life in Burke and Columbia counties. </abstract>
         <langmaterial id="aspace_4e0894b31e10398c7d7fd47ff7d1d686">Materials in
            English</langmaterial>
